Key Match Events: Harry Brook scored an unbeaten 110 off 94 balls to help England reach 304-4
Will Jacks and Ben Duckett contributed half-centuries for England
Liam Livingstone hit 2 sixes in his 25-ball half-century
Mitchell Starc dismissed Phil Salt and Ben Duckett in the same over
Alex Carey and Aaron Hardie contributed 77 and 44 respectively for Australia
Mitchell Starc took 3 wickets for Australia
England won by 46 runs via the DLS method
Post-Match Reflections: Harry Brook praised his team's performance and their momentum
Mitchell Marsh admitted Australia's poor batting and conceded that they were off the radar in this game
Miscellaneous Highlights: Travis Head and Adam Zampa were rested for Australia
The series continues on Friday with the fourth ODI at Lord's
